 them as materials of the “Dutch cultural archive,” or the Dutch “reservoir” of sentiments, knowledge, fantasies, and beliefs about race and slavery that have shaped the dominant sense of the Dutch self up to the present day.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntislavery movementsxHistoryy18th centuryzNetherlands. 0aAntislavery movementsxHistoryy19th centuryzNetherlands. 0aTheater and societyxHistoryy18th centuryzNetherlands. 0aTheater and societyxHistoryy19th centuryzNetherlands. 0aTheaterxHistoryy18th centuryzNetherlands. 0aTheaterxHistoryy19th centuryzNetherlands. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aFestivals, Theatre, and Performance. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aLiterary Theory, Criticism, and History. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aHISTORY / Caribbean & West Indies / General.2bisacsh  a(Anti-)Slavery, Theatre, Race, the Netherlands, 1800.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048554829?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048554829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048554829/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2